## The Foundation That Everything Else Rests On

Day 86 established the capstone structure — nine sections, each with a synthesis goal and a specific integration insight to capture that the day-by-day development alone would not reveal. The capstone's purpose is to show that the components developed across 85 days form a coherent security program, not just a collection of well-executed individual activities.

Section 1 — System Description and Scope — is where the capstone earns its coherence. Every subsequent section (compliance mapping, risk summary, control implementation, policies, training, incident response, monitoring, POA&M) is bounded by what is defined here. If the scope is vague, every subsequent section inherits that vagueness. If the system description is accurate and current, every subsequent section can be traced back to it.

I also want to be honest about what makes the Day 87 system description different from what a fresh GRC plan would produce. A fresh plan starts from scratch — what is the system, who uses it, what data does it handle. This capstone system description starts from eight months of operational experience, SSP version 1.2, and a continuous monitoring program that has produced five significant findings and five POA&M closures. The system I am describing is not the authorized-day system — it is the system as it exists now, informed by everything the monitoring program has revealed.

