### Technical Architecture — Current State (SSP v1.2)

**Deployment environment:** Amazon Web Services (AWS), us-east-1 region (primary), with cross-region backup to us-west-2.

**Primary compute:** EC2 instance ([instance type], [current AMI version]) running Ubuntu [version] and Apache Tomcat [version] serving the OpenMRS application. Instance is deployed in a private subnet within the dedicated VPC; all inbound application traffic passes through the AWS WAF and Application Load Balancer before reaching the EC2 instance.

**Database:** RDS MySQL [version], deployed in a separate private subnet, accessible only from the EC2 instance's security group. Encryption at rest using customer-managed KMS key (openmrs-rds-encryption, ARN: [ARN]). Automated daily snapshots retained for 35 days. Point-in-time recovery enabled.

**Storage:** S3 bucket ([bucket name]) storing weekly full database exports for cross-region backup. Server-side encryption with AES-256. Object Lock in Compliance mode for backup objects. Cross-region replication to us-west-2.

**Network security:** VPC with public subnet (WAF/ALB) and private subnets (EC2, RDS) in separate availability zones. Security groups enforce least-privilege network access. VPC flow logs enabled. No direct internet access to EC2 or RDS instances.

**Identity and access management:** IAM roles and policies for all AWS service interactions. No long-term access keys in use for application functions (exception: CloudWatch agent IAM user — Low severity finding, optimization scheduled). MFA enforced for all IAM console access. Root account locked with TOTP MFA and no active access keys.

**Monitoring and detection:** AWS CloudTrail (all regions, log file validation enabled, S3 delivery with EventBridge tamper detection alert), AWS Config (22 managed rules, all currently COMPLIANT except one [date of last review]), AWS GuardDuty (enabled, Security Hub integration active), AWS Inspector (monthly automated assessment), AWS Security Hub (FSBP standard, NIST 800-53 standard, findings aggregation), AWS Audit Manager (NIST 800-53 and HIPAA frameworks, automated evidence collection).

**Changes since authorization:** The system architecture has not changed materially since the authorization date. Significant implementation changes reflected in SSP v1.2: CM-3 implementation description updated to document IAM policy modification notification gap and EventBridge expansion commitment; CP-9 implementation description updated with RTO trend note; AC-2 implementation description updated for internal role change notification requirement.

